Brazil to Pursue Inflation Target of 4.5%, Rousseff Tells Valor

-- B y   L a u r a   P r i c e
-- 
2011-03-17T11:30:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-17/brazil-to-pursue-inflation-target-of-4-5-rousseff-tells-valor.html
  Brazil ’s government will keep
pursuing the center of its inflation target of 4.5 percent,
President  Dilma Rousseff  told  Valor Economico .  The South American country isn’t growing beyond its capacity
and the government can control inflation while maintaining
“sustainable” growth, the Sao Paulo-based newspaper said,
citing Rousseff. The government needs to keep track of
accelerating inflation in services, she told the paper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
